1082
00:59:37,620 --> 00:59:38,953
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

1083
00:59:38,954 --> 00:59:39,872
Wow.

1084
00:59:41,331 --> 00:59:42,164
- Yes.
- Not like that.

1085
00:59:42,165 --> 00:59:43,625
I just meant, didn't know.

1086
00:59:43,626 --> 00:59:44,710
(SCOFFS) Thanks.

1087
00:59:45,002 --> 00:59:46,211
Yeah, ten years.

1088
00:59:48,589 --> 00:59:50,173
- Yeah.
- So divorced or...?

1089
00:59:50,799 --> 00:59:51,634
No, he died.

1090
00:59:53,218 --> 00:59:54,260
Oh, I'm sorry.

1091
00:59:54,261 --> 00:59:56,555
No, no. Don't be.
He was not very nice.

1092
00:59:58,181 --> 00:59:59,056
Yeah. I just...

1093
00:59:59,057 --> 01:00:01,351
I don't think
he knew how to love.

1094
01:00:02,019 --> 01:00:02,853
Yeah.

1095
01:00:03,604 --> 01:00:05,855
Yeah, I know how that feels.
(CLEARS THROAT)

1096
01:00:05,856 --> 01:00:06,982
Oh, yeah?

1097
01:00:07,816 --> 01:00:08,651
Yeah.

1098
01:00:09,777 --> 01:00:11,278
Yeah, my parents, uh...

1099
01:00:11,862 --> 01:00:12,821
...were the same.

1100
01:00:13,321 --> 01:00:14,865
Both with each other and me.

1101
01:00:15,658 --> 01:00:17,075
Dad was a total stranger.

1102
01:00:18,285 --> 01:00:20,538
I didn't know him. Couldn't
tell you one thing about him.

1103
01:00:21,872 --> 01:00:23,456
Was raised by my mom.

1104
01:00:24,625 --> 01:00:26,084
Very mean person.

1105
01:00:27,545 --> 01:00:29,337
Uh, like, abusive.

1106
01:00:29,797 --> 01:00:31,632
Emotionally, physically.

1107
01:00:34,510 --> 01:00:36,468
Yeah. Her father was
a piece of shit though,

1108
01:00:36,469 --> 01:00:38,888
so, I try not to blame her, but,

1109
01:00:38,889 --> 01:00:42,768
it's hard to not resent her,
you know?

1110
01:00:48,607 --> 01:00:50,692
You ever hear that saying, uh,

1111
01:00:50,693 --> 01:00:53,195
"monsters aren't born,
they're created"?

1112
01:00:55,155 --> 01:00:56,155
(CHUCKLES)

1113
01:00:56,156 --> 01:00:58,491
Yeah. What?
Are you calling me a monster?

1114
01:00:59,702 --> 01:01:01,203
Oh, yeah.
You're a monster, all right.

1115
01:01:01,745 --> 01:01:04,623
(CHUCKLES)
Yeah. Yeah, I am.

1116
01:01:05,373 --> 01:01:06,208
I am.

1117
01:01:07,000 --> 01:01:08,418
At least now we know...

1118
01:01:09,795 --> 01:01:13,006
...it's not your fault.
(CHUCKLES)

1119
01:01:18,679 --> 01:01:21,098
Did you ever think about
leaving him? Your husband?

1120
01:01:23,767 --> 01:01:24,602
BRADLEY: Yeah.

1121
01:01:26,061 --> 01:01:26,979
Every night.

1122
01:01:28,772 --> 01:01:29,815
For years.

1123
01:01:32,860 --> 01:01:36,321
I just kept hoping
he'd change, and...

1124
01:01:37,239 --> 01:01:40,909
...just go back to how it was
in the beginning. (SCOFFS)

1125
01:01:41,910 --> 01:01:43,911
You know, you just,
you lie to yourself,

1126
01:01:43,912 --> 01:01:46,915
because you don't
want to be alone.

1127
01:01:52,630 --> 01:01:53,756
How'd he die?

1128
01:01:57,009 --> 01:01:58,135
Car accident.

1129
01:02:02,014 --> 01:02:03,265
He was a drinker.

1130
01:02:05,893 --> 01:02:07,269
And, uh...

1131
01:02:08,729 --> 01:02:11,565
...I'd always hide his keys when
he got really, really drunk.

1132
01:02:13,692 --> 01:02:16,612
And one night...
well, that night...

1133
01:02:17,613 --> 01:02:18,947
we had a big fight.

1134
01:02:21,116 --> 01:02:23,368
And he did some things
he shouldn't have.

1135
01:02:25,954 --> 01:02:27,247
Awful things.

1136
01:02:30,042 --> 01:02:31,209
Even for him.

1137
01:02:34,337 --> 01:02:37,007
And he had
this full head of steam.

1138
01:02:38,008 --> 01:02:40,135
He was looking for those keys.

1139
01:02:43,764 --> 01:02:45,432
So, I took them out of my purse.

1140
01:02:47,851 --> 01:02:48,977
Put them on the table.

1141
01:02:51,730 --> 01:02:52,690
Let him go.

1142
01:02:55,150 --> 01:02:56,777
Poured him his last drink.

1143
01:03:06,579 --> 01:03:08,538
Can't believe I told you that.
(CHUCKLES)

1144
01:03:08,539 --> 01:03:09,456
It's okay.

1145
01:03:11,875 --> 01:03:13,376
I've never told anyone that.

1146
01:03:23,303 --> 01:03:24,137
You know what?

1147
01:03:25,055 --> 01:03:26,765
I don't think
we should ever leave here.

1148
01:03:29,560 --> 01:03:30,603
You know what I mean?

1149
