if I could use that knife.

1209
01:08:19,057 --> 01:08:20,142
Yeah.

1210
01:08:20,601 --> 01:08:22,728
But you should really
learn to do it without.

1211
01:08:24,104 --> 01:08:26,355
Take a crack at it, solve it.

1212
01:08:26,356 --> 01:08:27,315
Prove me wrong.

1213
01:08:27,650 --> 01:08:29,317
Didn't you say that to me once?

1214
01:08:29,652 --> 01:08:32,029
Ah. Very good.

1215
01:08:34,489 --> 01:08:35,533
(SIGHS)

1216
01:08:36,158 --> 01:08:36,992
All right.

1217
01:08:38,368 --> 01:08:40,913
Leg's getting a little stiff.
I'm gonna take it for a walk.

1218
01:08:41,496 --> 01:08:43,165
I think I'm gonna try to
get to the high ridge today.

1219
01:08:44,499 --> 01:08:46,793
- That's pretty far.
- (SIGHS)

1220
01:08:46,794 --> 01:08:49,211
Watch out for those poison vines
on the south side, remember?

1221
01:08:49,212 --> 01:08:50,130
Yup.

1222
01:08:50,673 --> 01:08:51,507
You know what?

1223
01:08:51,965 --> 01:08:52,883
I'll join you.

1224
01:08:54,635 --> 01:08:55,468
BRADLEY: Sure.

1225
01:08:55,928 --> 01:08:57,638
Need some exercise myself.

1226
01:08:58,681 --> 01:09:00,473
BRADLEY: <i>Hey, I wanted
to thank you, by the way.</i>

1227
01:09:00,891 --> 01:09:01,725
LINDA: <i>For?</i>

1228
01:09:02,184 --> 01:09:04,227
BRADLEY: <i>Just all the things
you've taught me out here.</i>

1229
01:09:05,020 --> 01:09:06,395
<i>Just in case, you know,</i>

1230
01:09:06,396 --> 01:09:09,232
<i>they find us soon,
or this comes to an end.</i>

1231
01:09:10,108 --> 01:09:12,819
Wanted you to know
the time here, for me,

1232
01:09:12,820 --> 01:09:14,697
it wasn't wasted.

1233
01:09:16,532 --> 01:09:18,241
Yeah. I feel the same way.

1234
01:09:22,663 --> 01:09:23,872
(CHUCKLES)

1235
01:09:25,833 --> 01:09:26,959
Can I make you dinner?

1236
01:09:28,085 --> 01:09:29,002
Tomorrow night?

1237
01:09:30,253 --> 01:09:31,629
Get you outta the kitchen
for a change?

1238
01:09:31,630 --> 01:09:32,630
- (CHUCKLES)
- What do you think?

1239
01:09:32,631 --> 01:09:34,883
Well, that would be nice.

1240
01:09:46,394 --> 01:09:48,980
Good evening, madam. Thank you
for dining with us tonight.

1241
01:09:48,981 --> 01:09:51,315
LINDA:
Oh, my goodness. Look at that!

1242
01:09:51,316 --> 01:09:53,109
For starters,
we have a mango salsa,

1243
01:09:53,110 --> 01:09:55,738
accompanied by Marian plums,
freshly picked.

1244
01:09:56,614 --> 01:09:57,989
And for the main course,
we have a beautiful white fish.

1245
01:09:57,990 --> 01:10:01,702
A smoked barramundi
with a wild lemon grass garnish.

1246
01:10:01,827 --> 01:10:03,286
(CHUCKLES)

1247
01:10:04,705 --> 01:10:06,706
W-Wonderful.

1248
01:10:06,707 --> 01:10:08,000
<i>Bon appétit.</i>

1249
01:10:08,584 --> 01:10:11,210
Uh, do you,
do you cook much at home or...?

1250
01:10:11,211 --> 01:10:13,212
No. No. Never.

1251
01:10:13,213 --> 01:10:17,258
We either order out
or go to dinner.

1252
01:10:17,259 --> 01:10:19,761
Occasionally, we'll have
like a chef come and cook for us

1253
01:10:19,762 --> 01:10:21,639
- if we wanna get fancy.
- Wow. Mmm.

1254
01:10:22,222 --> 01:10:25,601
That's you and your fiancée,
Zuri?

1255
01:10:27,269 --> 01:10:28,186
Zuri, yeah.

1256
01:10:29,855 --> 01:10:31,231
You must miss her, huh?

1257
01:10:32,691 --> 01:10:33,526
Yeah.

1258
01:10:43,786 --> 01:10:44,620
You okay?

1259
01:10:47,164 --> 01:10:49,291
(GROANS) Feeling a little, uh...

1260
01:10:51,919 --> 01:10:54,254
(ECHOING) ...dizzy, actually.

1261
01:10:54,713 --> 01:10:56,256
(ECHOING)
Maybe you should lay down.

1262
01:10:57,007 --> 01:10:59,718
(ECHOING) Yeah.

1263
01:11:00,844 --> 01:11:03,889
(GROANS)

1264
01:11:05,891 --> 01:11:07,976
(COUGHING)

1265
01:11:09,019 --> 01:11:10,771
(INTENSE GROANING)

1266
01:11:16,151 --> 01:11:18,820
(GASPING) What?

1267
01:11:18,821 --> 01:11:20,906
(GROANING)

1268
01:11:26,704 --> 01:11:28,495
LINDA: (GROANING)

1269
01:11:28,496 --> 01:11:30,541
(LAUGHS)

1270
01:11:31,584 --> 01:11:35,838
(GROANS) No!

1271
01:11:38,215 --> 01:11:40,050
(PANTING)

1272
01:11:50,978 --> 01:11:53,105
(GRUNTS)

1273
01:11:58,068 --> 01:12:02,864
(SHOUTS, CACKLES)

1274
01:12:02,865 --> 01:12:04,240
Yes!

1275
01:12:04,241 --> 01:12:05,575
Fuck you, Linda!

1276
01:12:05,576 --> 01:12:07,661
(COUGHING)

1277
01:12:10,163 --> 01:12:13,083
(GRUNTING)

1278
01:12:14,292 --> 01:12:15,835
(GRUNTS)

1279
01:12:15,836 --> 01:12:16,962
No, no, no, no!

1280
01:12:18,171 --> 01:12:19,798
Fuck! (GRUNTS)

1281
01:12:21,008 --> 01:12:21,967
(GASPS)

1282
01:12:23,761 --> 01:12:25,012
(SCREAMS)

1283
01:12:26,054 --> 01:12:27,890
(GROANING)

1284
01:12:38,984 --> 01:12:40,861
(GROANS)

1285
01:12:59,087 --> 01:13:00,379
Aw...

1286
01:13:00,380 --> 01:13:02,090
baby.

1287
01:13:03,926 --> 01:13:05,719
(RETCHES)

1288
01:13:10,766 --> 01:13:12,225
(GROANS)

1289
01:13:16,229 --> 01:13:17,730
(GRUNTING)

1290
01:13:17,731 --> 01:13:19,357
LINDA: (GRUNTING)

1291
01:13:22,485 --> 01:13:23,736
BRADLEY: (MUMBLES)

1292
01:13:23,737 --> 01:13:26,364
(RETCHES)

1293
01:13:27,866 --> 01:13:28,700
(GRUNTS)

1294
01:13:28,701 --> 01:13:30,410
(PANTING)

1295
01:13:37,292 --> 01:13:38,126
(GRUNTING)

1296
01:13:42,881 --> 01:13:45,509
I really was just trying
to knock you out. I wasn't...

1297
01:13:46,343 --> 01:13:48,220
I swear to God, you know...

1298
01:13:49,179 --> 01:13:50,429
I wasn't trying to...

1299
01:13:50,430 --> 01:13:52,181
- LINDA: Just stop.
- It was just...

1300
01:13:52,182 --> 01:13:55,351
You don't have to keep
saying that. I-I believe you.

1301
01:13:55,352 --> 01:13:56,353
Mmm.

1302
01:13:57,813 --> 01:13:59,147
LINDA: (EXHALES)

1303
01:14:00,273 --> 01:14:01,149
(SOBS)

1304
01:14:03,611 --> 01:14:06,446
LINDA: I tasted something
bitter, but I just... (SCOFFS)

1305
01:14:07,489 --> 01:14:08,865
I really didn't want to think

1306
01:14:08,866 --> 01:14:10,450
you could
do something like that.

1307
01:14:11,493 --> 01:14:12,369
But...

1308
01:14:13,829 --> 01:14:14,954
Anyway, you know what,

1309
01:14:14,955 --> 01:14:17,248
it would take a hell of a lot
more berries than that to...

1310
01:14:17,249 --> 01:14:18,584
kill a human being.

1311
01:14:19,126 --> 01:14:19,960
Yeah.

1312
01:14:20,252 --> 01:14:21,168
LINDA: For next time.

1313
01:14:21,169 --> 01:14:24,255
I even screwed that up.
(CHUCKLES)

1314
01:14:24,256 --> 01:14:25,464
Such an idiot.

1315
01:14:25,465 --> 01:14:28,218
- BRADLEY: (CRYING)
- (SHUSHING)

1316
01:14:31,138 --> 01:14:32,055
It's okay.

1317
01:14:32,430 --> 01:14:34,015
- I get it.
- (SOBS)

1318
01:14:34,016 --> 01:14:35,643
Here, here, here.

1319
01:14:36,184 --> 01:14:38,353
Come on, let's get
your strength back, huh?

1320
01:14:39,271 --> 01:14:40,188
Again.

1321
01:14:40,814 --> 01:14:41,732
(WHIMPERING) Okay.

1322
01:14:43,776 --> 01:14:45,235
- There you go.
- Mmm.

1323
01:14:45,653 --> 01:14:46,486
Yeah.

1324
01:14:47,530 --> 01:14:48,864
(SIGHS)

1325
01:14:49,406 --> 01:14:52,868
Now, some things are gonna
have to change with you.

1326
01:14:53,786 --> 01:14:56,162
- And it's not gonna be easy.
- Definitely.

1327
01:14:56,163 --> 01:14:57,455
Yeah.

1328
01:14:58,248 --> 01:15:00,875
(GROANS)
I've really been thinking

1329
01:15:00,876 --> 01:15:03,128
how I can get through to you.

1330
01:15:03,712 --> 01:15:05,838
Do you want some?
You haven't eaten.

1331
01:15:05,839 --> 01:15:07,173
I'm okay, thanks.

1332
01:15:07,174 --> 01:15:08,634
- You sure?
- Yeah.

1333
01:15:09,092 --> 01:15:10,553
Still have a queasy tummy.

1334
01:15:11,554 --> 01:15:12,555
Right.

1335
01:15:14,014 --> 01:15:15,139
- I know how hard...
- So stupid.

1336
01:15:15,140 --> 01:15:16,517
...this all must be for you.

1337
01:15:17,768 --> 01:15:19,562
Not being in control.

1338
01:15:20,312 --> 01:15:22,229
- Ahh.
- You're not used to...

1339
01:15:22,230 --> 01:15:24,441
- (CLICKING TONGUE)
- being in this, shall we say,

1340
01:15:25,483 --> 01:15:27,234
...submissive position.

1341
01:15:27,235 --> 01:15:29,236
(CLICKING TONGUE)

1342
01:15:29,237 --> 01:15:30,237
I mean, it's natural

1343
01:15:30,238 --> 01:15:32,031
for you not to be able
to take orders from me.

1344
01:15:32,032 --> 01:15:35,660
To have to depend on me
for your survival.

1345
01:15:35,661 --> 01:15:37,079
- You know?
- (WHEEZES)

1346
01:15:37,830 --> 01:15:38,789
It's just natural.

1347
01:15:39,456 --> 01:15:41,457
You're a slave to your biology.

1348
01:15:41,458 --> 01:15:43,544
- (GURGLE)
- Oh!

1349
01:15:44,670 --> 01:15:46,463
Feeling kinda funny, huh?

1350
01:15:47,255 --> 01:15:48,841
- Can't move?
- (WHEEZES)

1351
01:15:49,341 --> 01:15:53,095
That's the neurotoxins
from this blue-ringed octopus.

1352
01:15:54,304 --> 01:15:57,975
Blocks the transmission
of nerve impulses.

1353
01:15:59,434 --> 01:16:01,061
Caught it about a week ago.

1354
01:16:02,062 --> 01:16:05,065
Was really hoping I wouldn't
have to use it, but...

1355
01:16:05,691 --> 01:16:07,067
...held on to it.

1356
01:16:08,318 --> 01:16:09,653
Just in case.

1357
01:16:11,697 --> 01:16:13,197
(SIGHS)

1358
01:16:13,198 --> 01:16:16,242
Now, you did a great job
with that raft. I gotta say.

1359
01:16:16,243 --> 01:16:17,703
You really are a quick study.

1360
01:16:19,121 --> 01:16:21,624
But if you really wanted it
to hold...

1361
01:16:21,915 --> 01:16:23,040
(SLURS INDISTINCTLY)

1362
01:16:23,041 --> 01:16:26,504
...you should have used
double floor lashing.

1363
01:16:27,838 --> 01:16:29,590
But, of course,
I never taught you that one.

1364
01:16:30,173 --> 01:16:31,049
Shoot.

1365
01:16:32,593 --> 01:16:33,760
(SIGHS)

1366
01:16:33,761 --> 01:16:37,347
Now, I just want to put
your mind at ease, okay?

1367
01:16:38,181 --> 01:16:41,476
The toxins from
the <i>Hapalochlaena lunulata</i>

1368
01:16:42,102 --> 01:16:43,395
aren't gonna kill you.

1369
01:16:44,396 --> 01:16:46,898
And I promise
they will wear off.

1370
01:16:46,899 --> 01:16:49,401
But right now, you won't be able
to move or feel anything.

1371
01:16:50,110 --> 01:16:52,153
And trust me...
(SIGHS)

1372
01:16:52,154 --> 01:16:53,781
...I think you want it that way.

1373
01:16:54,907 --> 01:16:56,116
Ooh.

1374
01:17:04,667 --> 01:17:05,876
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

1375
01:17:06,919 --> 01:17:08,170
Where was I?

1376
01:17:08,879 --> 01:17:13,841
So, when I was a little girl,
we had this dog.

1377
01:17:13,842 --> 01:17:15,426
BRADLEY: (GRUNTS)

1378
01:17:15,427 --> 01:17:18,596
Very, very naughty dog.
So disobedient.

1379
01:17:18,597 --> 01:17:21,642
- (WHIMPERS)
- Always running away.

1380
01:17:23,476 --> 01:17:24,310
(GRUNTS)

1381
01:17:24,311 --> 01:17:28,314
And my dad said,
"It's not his fault.

1382
01:17:28,315 --> 01:17:30,817
(CHUCKLES)
He just..."

1383
01:17:30,818 --> 01:17:32,194
(GRUNTS)

1384
01:17:33,236 --> 01:17:35,989
(SIGHS)
"...needs to be fixed."

1385
01:17:41,870 --> 01:17:42,913
Now...

1386
01:17:44,164 --> 01:17:46,750
- it's actually quite a simple...
- (METAL SCRAPES)

1387
01:17:48,001 --> 01:17:49,252
...medical procedure.

1388
01:17:49,628 --> 01:17:52,840
They used to do it
all the time to Egyptian slaves.

1389
01:17:53,423 --> 01:17:56,218
Made them more, um, obedient.

1390
01:17:56,927 --> 01:17:58,762
- Compliant.
- (WHIMPERS)

1391
01:18:01,515 --> 01:18:02,516
(WHISPERS) Okay.

1392
01:18:05,352 --> 01:18:06,812
No help is coming.

1393
01:18:08,438 --> 01:18:10,524
This is the way things are now.

1394
01:18:10,941 --> 01:18:13,151
And you need
to just accept that.

1395
01:18:14,612 --> 01:18:16,196
You are stuck.

1396
01:18:17,072 --> 01:18:18,156
No power.

1397
01:18:18,616 --> 01:18:20,534
Low end of the totem pole.

1398
01:18:21,827 --> 01:18:23,912
With some asshole boss.

1399
01:18:24,663 --> 01:18:26,123
Just like I was.

1400
01:18:27,124 --> 01:18:28,833
Although, I'm betting...

1401
01:18:28,834 --> 01:18:32,170
I am a much nicer boss
than you ever would have been.

1402
01:18:34,422 --> 01:18:37,593
(GASPS)
Except for maybe this part.

1403
01:18:40,345 --> 01:18:41,304
Ready?

1404
01:18:43,140 --> 01:18:44,975
(MUFFLED WHINING)

1405
01:18:45,809 --> 01:18:48,144
- (GASPS)
- (SQUELCHING)

1406
01:18:48,145 --> 01:18:49,521
- Okay.
- (MUFFLED YELP)

1407
01:18:49,522 --> 01:18:51,105
Now, now, don't be a baby.

1408
01:18:51,106 --> 01:18:52,691
You're not gonna miss
this stuff.

1409
01:18:53,776 --> 01:18:56,111
- (KNIFE CLINKS)
- (SUSTAINED YELP)

1410
01:18:56,612 --> 01:18:58,195
(YELPS)

1411
01:18:58,196 --> 01:19:01,490
- (KNIFE SLICING)
- (MUFFLED WAILING)

1412
01:19:01,491 --> 01:19:03,325
- (WAILS)
- Ooh!

1413
01:19:03,326 --> 01:19:05,620
(MUFFLED WAILING)

1414
01:19:05,621 --> 01:19:07,496
(CHUCKLES)
We got a bleeder here.

1415
01:19:07,497 --> 01:19:09,624
- (YELPS)
- (BRIGHTLY) A lot of blood.

1416
01:19:09,625 --> 01:19:11,292
- (GROANING)
- (CHUCKLING) Wow.

1417
01:19:11,293 --> 01:19:14,755
(GROANING)

1418
01:19:15,548 --> 01:19:16,757
Oh.

1419
01:19:17,758 --> 01:19:19,176
(SIGHS)

1420
01:19:20,886 --> 01:19:22,262
(MUFFLED CRY)

1421
01:19:23,055 --> 01:19:25,140
- It's okay. It's just a rat.
- (GROANS)

1422
01:19:26,016 --> 01:19:27,309
- (GROANS)
- (RAT SPLATTERS)

1423
01:19:30,478 --> 01:19:32,439
Next time it won't be a rat.

1424
01:19:34,650 --> 01:19:38,445
So, don't ever mistake
my kindness for weakness.

1425
01:19:39,613 --> 01:19:45,536
(GRUNTING)

1426
01:19:53,460 --> 01:19:54,628
Hey, there!

1427
01:19:55,713 --> 01:19:57,047
How goes it?

1428
01:20:00,509 --> 01:20:02,845
Barely talked in two days,
you Gloomy Gus.

1429
01:20:06,974 --> 01:20:09,267
Would it kill you
to give me a little smile?

1430
01:20:17,776 --> 01:20:19,778
Mmm. There it is.

1431
01:20:20,946 --> 01:20:22,823
Tell you what I'm gonna do
to cheer you up.

1432
01:20:23,657 --> 01:20:25,117
I'm gonna go find...

1433
01:20:26,034 --> 01:20:29,328
the juiciest, most beautiful
fruits on this whole island

1434
01:20:29,329 --> 01:20:30,914
and make you a little treat.

1435
01:20:36,461 --> 01:20:38,337
Such a sourpuss.

1436
01:20:38,338 --> 01:20:41,340
Make him a little fire,
and he's gonna come around.

1437
01:20:41,341 --> 01:20:43,802
(ENGINE HUMMING)

1438
01:20:49,349 --> 01:20:52,520
(GASPS)

1439
01:20:54,730 --> 01:20:57,023
ZURI: Hello? Hello?

1440
01:20:57,024 --> 01:20:58,150
Shit.

1441
01:21:00,528 --> 01:21:02,695
Linda! It's me.

1442
01:21:02,696 --> 01:21:05,698
(RAPIDLY) Shit, shit,
shit, shit, shit, shit...

1443
01:21:05,699 --> 01:21:09,744
Oh, my God! We found her!
I did it. I can't believe it.

1444
01:21:09,745 --> 01:21:10,996
Hey.

1445
01:21:12,330 --> 01:21:13,623
- Hey.
- No, no, no.

1446
01:21:13,624 --> 01:21:14,624
(EXAGGERATED GIGGLE)

1447
01:21:14,625 --> 01:21:16,501
- Come here!
- (GIGGLE CONTINUES)

1448
01:21:16,502 --> 01:21:17,835
ZURI: Oh, my God.

1449
01:21:17,836 --> 01:21:19,963
Hi. Hello.

1450
01:21:21,339 --> 01:21:23,299
Is he alive? Is he here?

1451
01:21:23,300 --> 01:21:24,300
How on earth?

1452
01:21:24,301 --> 01:21:26,594
Bradley, is he-- is he here?

1453
01:21:26,595 --> 01:21:27,637
- Yes.
- He is?

1454
01:21:27,638 --> 01:21:29,305
- Yes, he's here.
- Oh, my God.

1455
01:21:29,306 --> 01:21:30,974
- He is here.
- He's alive!

1456
01:21:32,017 --> 01:21:33,893
Even when they called off
the search in this area,

1457
01:21:33,894 --> 01:21:35,352
I never gave up.

1458
01:21:35,353 --> 01:21:37,689
- I couldn't give up.
- That's amazing.

1459
01:21:37,690 --> 01:21:40,024
I hired my own boat,
I did my own search.

1460
01:21:40,025 --> 01:21:42,318
Is he okay? Is he hurt? Is he...

1461
01:21:42,319 --> 01:21:43,612
He's fine.

1462
01:21:44,487 --> 01:21:47,323
- He's so good. He's great.
- Great.

1463
01:21:47,324 --> 01:21:49,158
I can't believe
this is happening.

1464
01:21:49,159 --> 01:21:50,993
- I know.
- (CACKLES)

1465
01:21:50,994 --> 01:21:52,912
Please, can you take me to him?
Right now?

1466
01:21:52,913 --> 01:21:55,039
- I need to see him. Please.
- He's, um...

1467
01:21:55,040 --> 01:21:56,040
Is he just down here?

1468
01:21:56,041 --> 01:21:57,166
- Yes, he's out here.
- Yeah? He is?

1469
01:21:57,167 --> 01:21:58,543
No, no, no.

1470
01:21:58,544 --> 01:21:59,836
- He's not over there.
- Bradley, I'm here!

1471
01:21:59,837 --> 01:22:01,713
- Um--
- Bradley, where are you?

1472
01:22:01,714 --> 01:22:03,173
MAN: Should we follow you?

1473
01:22:04,257 --> 01:22:05,342
This way?

1474
01:22:07,010 --> 01:22:07,969
(SIGHS)

1475
01:22:07,970 --> 01:22:09,387
Should we follow you?

1476
01:22:09,680 --> 01:22:10,806
Uh...

1477
01:22:11,389 --> 01:22:14,266
- I just need to get my stuff.
- You're not gonna need this.

1478
01:22:14,267 --> 01:22:15,602
- (SMACKS)
- Ow.

1479
01:22:15,603 --> 01:22:18,355
- Sorry. Sorry, I just...
- You like mango, right?

1480
01:22:18,897 --> 01:22:19,814
Yeah, I worked really hard.

1481
01:22:19,815 --> 01:22:21,734
We got lots of food on the boat.

1482
01:22:23,861 --> 01:22:24,820
Oh, yum.

1483
01:22:25,863 --> 01:22:26,864
Yum, yum, yum.

1484
01:22:27,405 --> 01:22:28,532
Lead the way.

1485
01:22:29,199 --> 01:22:32,244
So, is it just the two of you?

1486
01:22:33,120 --> 01:22:35,538
Or is there a whole search party
waiting for us?

1487
01:22:35,539 --> 01:22:36,665
MAN: Just us.

1488
01:22:37,332 --> 01:22:40,752
But there will be many people
happy to hear you two are alive.

1489
01:22:40,753 --> 01:22:41,836
Once I radio back.

1490
01:22:41,837 --> 01:22:44,172
You'll be back in your own bed
in no time.

1491
01:22:44,882 --> 01:22:46,842
There's a shortcut
just ahead here.

1492
01:22:57,185 --> 01:22:59,937
ZURI: I bet you can't wait
to return to your life.

1493
01:22:59,938 --> 01:23:03,482
Your job, your family,
your friends.

1494
01:23:03,483 --> 01:23:05,277
(MAN SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)

1495
01:23:28,341 --> 01:23:30,553
Uh, shoelace.

1496
01:23:31,428 --> 01:23:32,387
Okay.

1497
01:23:32,721 --> 01:23:35,598
- Just follow the trail.
- ZURI: Yeah.

1498
01:23:35,599 --> 01:23:37,184
I'm right behind you.

1499
01:23:47,444 --> 01:23:50,823
(SLOWED BREATHING)

1500
01:23:56,579 --> 01:23:58,705
(SCREAMS)

1501
01:23:58,706 --> 01:24:00,665
Zuri! Zuri! Zuri! Come on!

1502
01:24:00,666 --> 01:24:03,626
- ZURI: (GRUNTING)
- Grab my hand. Hey. Come on!

1503
01:24:03,627 --> 01:24:06,212
I got you. I got you.
You can do it. You can do it.

1504
01:24:06,213 --> 01:24:07,922
Help me! Help me!

1505
01:24:07,923 --> 01:24:09,674
- ZURI: (GROANS)
- Come on. Come on.

1506
01:24:09,675 --> 01:24:11,008
I got you!

1507
01:24:11,009 --> 01:24:12,301
- Zuri! Come on.
- ZURI: Linda, help us!

1508
01:24:12,302 --> 01:24:14,386
I got you. You can do it.
You can do it.

1509
01:24:14,387 --> 01:24:16,055
I got you. You can do it.

1510
01:24:16,056 --> 01:24:17,724
Man: (GROANING)

1511
01:24:17,725 --> 01:24:19,100
Help me!

1512
01:24:19,101 --> 01:24:20,352
- Linda!
- Linda!

1513
01:24:20,811 --> 01:24:22,186
MAN: Help us!

1514
01:24:22,187 --> 01:24:24,940
ZURI: Linda!

1515
01:24:36,451 --> 01:24:37,661
Dinner.

1516
01:24:39,121 --> 01:24:40,122
Yep.

1517
01:24:43,834 --> 01:24:45,210
(SIGHS)

1518
01:25:22,956 --> 01:25:25,834
(RAIN PATTERING)

1519
01:25:31,799 --> 01:25:34,134
Saw some fresh boar tracks
earlier today.

1520
01:25:35,468 --> 01:25:37,137
We haven't had protein
in awhile.

1521
01:25:38,681 --> 01:25:40,683
Maybe when it clears up
we should go hunting.

1522
01:25:44,477 --> 01:25:46,104
I'm taking a sick day.

1523
01:25:49,316 --> 01:25:50,734
Can't do it on my own.

1524
01:26:24,476 --> 01:26:28,021
(SIGHS)

1525
01:26:33,736 --> 01:26:35,779
ZURI: (DISTANTLY) Linda!

1526
01:27:04,725 --> 01:27:08,145
(GROANS)

1527
01:27:11,524 --> 01:27:14,109
(GASPING)

1528
01:27:23,243 --> 01:27:27,039
(STRAINED GROANS)

1529
01:27:29,041 --> 01:27:32,002
(GASPING)

1530
01:27:38,466 --> 01:27:39,718
(GRUNTING FEEBLY)

1531
01:27:42,054 --> 01:27:43,597
(WAILING) Linda.

1532
01:27:44,973 --> 01:27:47,059
Linda!

1533
01:27:48,435 --> 01:27:50,853
You tried to kill me.

1534
01:27:50,854 --> 01:27:52,690
- No.
- Why?

1535
01:27:53,691 --> 01:27:54,900
(CRYING) Why?

1536
01:27:55,568 --> 01:27:57,110
Why'd you do it?

1537
01:27:58,737 --> 01:28:02,281
(GROANS) Why?
(CRYING)

1538
01:28:02,282 --> 01:28:04,283
Why'd you have to come?

1539
01:28:04,284 --> 01:28:05,577
I'm gonna tell Bradley
everything.

1540
01:28:05,578 --> 01:28:06,493
No.

1541
01:28:06,494 --> 01:28:08,037
- You're a murderer.
- No.

1542
01:28:08,038 --> 01:28:09,413
- You are!
- (SCREAMS)

1543
01:28:09,414 --> 01:28:11,499
(GRUNTING)

1544
01:28:14,044 --> 01:28:15,212
(GASPS)

